# create-blit-tech CLAUDE Is Canonical

- Treat `CLAUDE.md` at the repository root as canonical for work in this repo.
- Follow its monorepo layout, scaffold conventions, and command set.
- Generated game templates use plain JavaScript and beginner-friendly comments; do not apply library-only TypeScript conventions to template JS files.
- Public engine API names in generated games must match sibling repo `blit-tech` (`BT.isDown`, `isOverlayEnabled`, etc.).
- Use repo commands exactly as documented in `CLAUDE.md` (`pnpm run preflight`, not bare `pnpm preflight`).
